# auto-ascii

A Python package that converts an image to ASCII art.

## Installation

You can install this package locally:

```bash
pip install .
```

## Usage

### Command Line

Once installed, you can use the `auto-ascii` command in your terminal:

```bash
auto-ascii path/to/image.jpg --width 120
```

### In Python

You can also use it in your own Python scripts:

```python
from auto_ascii import image_to_ascii

ascii_art = image_to_ascii("path/to/image.jpg", new_width=100)
print(ascii_art)
```
